quran[19]{c,v,t,f}:
  79,46,"It will be, on the Day they see it,{1} as though they had not remained [in the world] except for an afternoon or a morning thereof.",1:[i.e., the Hour, the Resurrection.]
  83,31,"And when they returned to their people, they would return jesting."
  83,32,"And when they saw them, they would say, "
  83,33,"But they had not been sent as guardians over them."
  87,16,"But you prefer the worldly life,"
  87,17,"While the Hereafter is better and more enduring."
  87,18,"Indeed, this is in the former scriptures,"
  88,13,"Within it are couches raised high"
  88,14,"And cups put in place"
  88,15,"And cushions lined up"
  89,10,"And [with] Pharaoh, owner of the stakes?{1}",1:[By which he tortured people.]
  89,11,"[All of] whom oppressed within the lands"
  89,12,"And increased therein the corruption."
  90,4,"We have certainly created man into hardship."
  90,5,"Does he think that never will anyone overcome him?"
  90,6,"He says, "
  91,1,"By the sun and its brightness"
  91,2,"And [by] the moon when it follows it"
  91,3,"And [by] the day when it displays it{1}",1:[The earth. Also interpreted as the sun. The same applies to the following verse.]
